Package com.jml.core

Class ModelBucket

java.lang.Object
com.jml.core.ModelBucket
public class ModelBucket extends Object
A container for holding the results of a fitted model. This Object will hold different data depending on the model.

All data is accessed through the various get*(String) methods: 
     - getDoubleArr(String)
     - getDoubleArr2D(String)
     - getDouble(String)
     - getInteger(String)
If you need to get the Class of the object in the ModelBucket, you can use type(String)

      public Class type​(String key)
      Gets the class type of the object in this bucket associated with the given key.

      It is recommended to call containsKeyNotNull(String) before this method to ensure the key exists in this bucket. If the key does not exist, or if it exists and is null, this method will throw a null pointer exception.
